Identified by scraper @ 2024-11-08T12:22:42+00:00

  • Incident Date: 2024-11-04
  • City: SPOKANE
  • State: WA
  • Report Type: A hazardous material incident
  • Mode Of Transportation: Air
  • Carrier/Reporter: FEDERAL EXPRESS CORPORATION
  • Hazmat Fatalities: 0
  • Hazmat Injuries: 0
  • Non-Hazmat Fatalities: 0
  • Total Amount Of Damages: 0
  • Serious Incident Ind: No
  • Description: On 11/4/2024 at approximately 1015, Dangerous Goods Administration received a call from Employee 240946 at the station location in Spokane, reporting undeclared dangerous goods. The shipment consisted of 4 plastic bottles, packaged in a fiberboard box. The shipment was discovered emitting an odor during sort. Further investigation revealed a stain along the bottom of the box. Upon examining the inner contents, one of the bottles appeared damp around the closure. A safety data sheet found inside of the packaging classified the commodity as UN3082. It appears the shipment was tendered under IATA Special Provisions A197; however, the packaging of the shipment did not comply with IATA 5.0.2.6.1.3 and 5.0.2.8., not having sufficient closure, ullage, or absorbent material. The shipment is being held for an FAA investigation.

item.title: Report E-2024110004
item.description:
Report E-2024110004

Identified by scraper @ 2024-11-04T12:23:29+00:00

  • Incident Date: 2024-10-31
  • City: PASCO
  • State: WA
  • Report Type: A hazardous material incident
  • Mode Of Transportation: Highway
  • Carrier/Reporter: XPO LOGISTICS, LLC
  • Hazmat Fatalities: 0
  • Hazmat Injuries: 0
  • Non-Hazmat Fatalities: 0
  • Total Amount Of Damages: 6500
  • Serious Incident Ind: No
  • Description: XPO Logistics terminal UPW experienced a UN3149 Minncare HD Disinfectant release from a box containing (4) 1-gallon poly jugs. ERTS dispatched contractors to conduct cleanup operations. Contractors arrived onsite and confirmed approximately 1-gallon of product released to a 4’ x 4’ area of the concrete dock floor and pallet wood due to a forklift puncture. The impacted area was cleaned with absorbents. The damaged jug, impacted absorbents, PPE, and cardboard were placed into one 55-gallon poly drum. The impacted pallet wood, absorbents, and cardboard were placed into a second 55-gallon poly drum. The waste was staged onsite for terminal personnel to manage.
